Objective:
Predict which financial response (model_a vs model_b) is better for a given finance prompt, or whether it’s a tie.

Input → Output
•	Input (X): prompt, response_a, response_b
•	Output (y): winner_model_a, winner_model_b, winner_tie (3-class classification)

DL Type:
•	Supervised learning
•	Sequence modeling (LSTM)

Business / Research Metric:
•	Primary: Accuracy, ROC-AUC
•	Secondary: F1-score (especially for tie class, if minority)

Constraints:
•	Limited dataset (~13k) → small LSTM or pretrained embeddings recommended
•	Sequence length varies → padding/truncation needed
•	Interpretability (optional SHAP/attention)
